  <title>Styling Numbers Differently than Titles in Divisions</title>
  <info>
    <definitions definitionfile="defs.xml"/>
  </info>
  
  <section role="problem">
    <title>Problem</title>
    <para>You want to layout the number differently from the title. As
      such, you search for an solution how these information can be
      independently get.</para>
  </section>
  <section role="solution">
    <title>Solution</title>
    <para>The DocBook XSL stylesheets contain two modes which are 
      important in this regard: <literal>label.markup</literal>
      and <literal>title.markup</literal>.</para>
  </section>
  <section role="discussion">
    <title>Discussion</title>
    <para><remark>TDB</remark></para>
  </section>
